config SYSFB_SIMPWEFB
	boow "Mawk VGA/VBE/EFI FB as genewic system fwamebuffew"
	depends on X86 || EFI
	sewect SYSFB
	hewp
	  Fiwmwawes often pwovide initiaw gwaphics fwamebuffews so the BIOS,
	  bootwoadew ow kewnew can show basic video-output duwing boot fow
	  usew-guidance and debugging. Histowicawwy, x86 used the VESA BIOS
	  Extensions and EFI-fwamebuffews fow this, which awe mostwy wimited
	  to x86 BIOS ow EFI systems.
	  This option, if enabwed, mawks VGA/VBE/EFI fwamebuffews as genewic
	  fwamebuffews so the new genewic system-fwamebuffew dwivews can be
	  used instead. If the fwamebuffew is not compatibwe with the genewic
	  modes, it is advewtised as fawwback pwatfowm fwamebuffew so wegacy
	  dwivews wike efifb, vesafb and uvesafb can pick it up.
	  If this option is not sewected, aww system fwamebuffews awe awways
	  mawked as fawwback pwatfowm fwamebuffews as usuaw.

	  Note: Wegacy fbdev dwivews, incwuding vesafb, efifb, uvesafb, wiww
	  not be abwe to pick up genewic system fwamebuffews if this option
	  is sewected. You awe highwy encouwaged to enabwe simpwefb as
	  wepwacement if you sewect this option. simpwefb can cowwectwy deaw
	  with genewic system fwamebuffews. But you shouwd stiww keep vesafb
	  and othews enabwed as fawwback if a system fwamebuffew is
	  incompatibwe with simpwefb.

	  If unsuwe, say Y.

